      • addStudentsToCourses

        public void addStudentsToCourses()
                          throws java.lang.Exception
        seeks to add all students in a department to a departments courses evenly. First of all works out how many students fit into a courses evenly, then works out how many students are left. Then seeks to spread all students across all courses. Students course property is also set, so each student can see what modules they have.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • addTutorsToModules

        public void addTutorsToModules()
                        throws java.lang.Exception

        ADDS TUTORS TO MODULES

        First check if tutors have been initialised, if so randomly choose department staff to append to each tutor to a module on each course

        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • setCM

        public <T> void setCM​(java.util.ArrayList<T> rawData,
                      java.util.ArrayList<T> modifiedProperty,
                      int limit)

        SET COURSE/MODULES

        Set courses and modules to each department randomly, with a length which is justified via "limit"

        Type Parameters:
        T - Generic type (of Arraylist)
        Parameters:
        rawData - raw list to randomly select from
        modifiedProperty - property of object to be appended to
        limit - how large you want array to be
